BUSINESS INSIGHT REPORT

--> The East region generates the highest total sales of$44.98 M, making it the strongest revenue contributor. This indicates higher customer demand and better sales performance in this region compared to others.

--> The Electorincs category is the most profitable, generating a total profit of $57.49 M. This suggests strong margins and customer preference for products in this category.

--> Discounts have a noticeable impact on profitability. As discount levels increase, profit and profit margins generally decline. 
    High discounting reduces overall profit and in some cases may lead to very low or negative profitability, indicating that discounts should be applied carefully.

--> Based on the monthly trend analysis, November is the best-performing month with total sales of $27.28 , showing clear seasonality in customer purchasing behavior.


--> Key recommendations for management:
      -- Prioritize the East region with better inventory planning, faster fulfillment, and targeted marketing.
			-- Focus on expanding and promoting the Electronics category to maximize profit contribution.
			-- Implement controlled discount policies (set discount limits and avoid over-discounting high-margin products).
			-- Prepare for peak demand during November through better stock planning and promotional scheduling.
			-- Track KPIs regularly (Total Sales, Total Profit, Profit Margin, Discount %) to ensure sales growth remains profitable.
